 To marry a woman with whom one is best suited, the typical process of engagement is initiated by an advance action on the part of the initiator of the process by which the recipient is invited or otherwise acknowledged as worthy of receiving the advance action. The advance action is to ask the recipient of the advance action to marry them. In the case of the initiator being male, this entails the typical active behavior of approaching a female and engaging her in conversation, by which one is able to garner valuable
